content.problemStatement:
A comparator function is a boolean return-type function that determines the order in which we would sort the array.

If we want to sort the array in decreasing order, our comparator function will look like

`bool cmp(int a, int b) {
    if(a &gt; b) {
        return true;
    }
    else {
        return false;
    }
}
`TaskIn the function sort, you are given a 2-d array. 

Each index of the array holds 2 values, consider these values as the cartesian coordinates of a point in a 2-d plane. 

You need to sort these points in increasing order of their distance from the origin (0,0)(0,0)(0,0). 

If the distance is same, sort the points in the order of increasing x-coordinate. \
Implement the `cmp()` function to solve this problem.  

The distance is calculated using the distance formula in a 2-d plane.
